title: Tziporah takes a tumble

organizations.name: jonathon moran news corp australia network share share on twitter  tziporah malkah

text:
Tziporah Malkah sent packing from jungle camp on I’m A Celebrity ... Get Me Out Of Here! February 26, 2017 8:40pm Tziporah Malkah reacts to losing her place on the I’m a Celebrity team. Picture: Ten. Jonathon Moran News Corp Australia Network Share Share on Twitter 
TZIPORAH Malkah has been sent packing from the South African jungle. 
The former model, who used to be known as Kate Fischer, is the third contestant eliminated this season of I’m A Celebrity … Get Me Out Of Here! 
“Third time is a charm,” Malkah said. 
“This experience has been surprising. I always knew it was going to be quite brutal.” 
Malkah, 43, who was once engaged to James Packer, lasted four out of six weeks on the Channel Ten reality show. Thanks for the memories @TziporahMalkah , we've loved having you in the jungle! #ImACelebrityAU pic.twitter.com/ikrMhejftU — #ImACelebrityAU (@ImACelebrityAU) February 26, 2017 
She was one of the standout contestants, speaking openly about her life with stories including the fact she hadn’t had sex for six years, why she and Packer broke up and how she was ripped off $2 million by a rabbi when she lived in Los Angeles. 
“She is a very unusual creature,” reality star Ash Pollard said of Malkah. Tziporah Malkah while taking part in I'm a Celebrity, Get Me Out of Here! Picture: Channel 10 Source: Channel 10 
Malkah’s jungle journey was not without difficulty. She fell out with singer Natalie Bassingthwaighte and three time Olympian Lisa Curry early on in the series. 
Last week she had a massive blow up with model Kris Smith and tonight didn’t acknowledge him when she departed camp. The third campmate leaving the jungle is Tziporah. #ImACelebrityAU pic.twitter.com/UoDybaZrYU — #ImACelebrityAU (@ImACelebrityAU) February 26, 2017 
“Tziporah probably out of all of us would never have dreamt that six months ago she would be in this position and the first step I think to a life that is a bit more happy for her,” radio shock jock Steve Price said. 
* The journalist is in South Africa as a guest of Channel Ten.
